snippet.textDisplay:
Makes you wonder if all this consumerism and technological "advancement" is worth it.
8 billion dollars in AirPods sales not to mention all the competitors' sales naturally means tons and tons of waste, plastic, metals, minerals produced probably ending in landfill as new and improved versions come out.
Consumer needs feed innovation and we can thank capitalism for the luxuries of our world today but surely it's about time we evolve a little and dampen the greed.
